---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Drzone Cloud Field Notes">
  <section class="shell article-shell">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Cloud architecture notes with an SA operating cadence.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      This site is a lightweight home for reusable architecture thinking: review notes,
      migration patterns, service comparisons, and build logs.
    </p>

    <div class="article-body">
      <h2>Focus</h2>
      <p>
        The writing here is biased toward practical decisions: what to standardize,
        what to prototype, where to draw a security boundary, and how to keep cost and
        reliability visible while a system evolves.
      </p>

      <h2>Content Shape</h2>
      <p>
        Posts are Markdown or MDX files in the repository. Each post carries language,
        tags, and publish dates through frontmatter, so the site can grow into a
        multilingual knowledge base without changing the deployment model.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
